<p>What the hell why was there so much fog what happened to Ashton's friends who was the pink-suited Alagaddan standing in the center of the room what the fuck what the fuck <em>what the fuck</em>-</p>
<p>&quot;Easy. Relax. Breathe in,&quot; Ashton had taken for granted the sounds that came with breathing, because it was <em>immediately</em> obvious that despite miming the motions, the Alagaddan was utterly silent. &quot;Breathe out.&quot;</p>
<p>Dammit, this was the Ambassador wasn't it? Ashton was-</p>
<p>&quot;I'm not the Ambassador. Don't worry. You're Jack's friend, and I'm not gonna hurt y'all.&quot;</p>
<p>Oh god it could read their mind.</p>
<p>&quot;You're afraid I'll find somethin' you don't wanna share, yeah? Again: you're Jack's friend. A friend of Jack is a friend of mine.&quot; The Alagaddan put their hands out. &quot;Can you trust me, little black butterfly?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Uh&#8230; butterfly?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Listen, I dunno if you're dressed like a goth or if that's your day look. You wanna new nickname, I can get you a new nickname.&quot;</p>
<p>Ashton's face scrunched itself. &quot;Ash works.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Right on, Ash, right on.&quot; The Alagaddan stretched, before collapsing to sitting against thin air. &quot;Gettin' to the business at hand, seems you're a mind of many chains. Short-term says you wanna go home.&quot; The Alagaddan snapped their fingers, and a contract appeared to Ashton's left. &quot;Mid-term says you wanna impress your friends.&quot; Another snap, and a contract appeared to Ashton's right. &quot;Long-term&#8230; oh.&quot; The Alagaddan was most probably grinning. &quot;<em>Oh</em>.&quot;</p>
<p>Something cold pushed itself up from Ashton's stomach.</p>
<p>&quot;I always <em>adore</em> desires like that, little Ash.&quot; The Alagaddan got up from their &quot;seat&quot; to pace the room. &quot;Money, power, power<em>s</em>, all that stuff's <em>banal</em>. Banal for me, and as alllllll my clients are like to learn, banal for humans. Money's fake, power's fragile, and you can't thaumaturge your way outta unfulfilling lives.&quot; The Alagaddan stopped before two <em>very</em> familiar shadows. &quot;Y'all long for somethin' <em>deeper</em>. Somethin'&#8230; primal.&quot; Their hand brushed against the head of the taller of the distressingly familiar shadows. &quot;Somethin' that drives your every-&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;I don't agree to anything I will not be making a deal with you at this time I thank you for your time representative of Alagadda <em>please leave</em>.&quot;</p>
<p>The Alagaddan groaned. &quot;You're no fun, Ash. See ya.&quot;</p>
