<p>This wasn't her apartment! What the hell happened to everyone?!</p>
<p>&quot;To answer your question,&quot; more mind-reading bullshit. What else did Sara expect? &quot;Your friends and apartment are perfectly safe. When you get as big as I got, you learn when to mess with timespace. You'll be back to normal once we finish business, yeah?&quot;</p>
<p>Did cop rules apply to jinn? It couldn't have hurt to try. &quot;Am I free to leave?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Abso-lutely. I mean, if you go right now, you'll miss a once in a lifetime opportunity for career advancement.&quot;</p>
<p>Oh great, the jinn was a pyramid schemer. &quot;Can you draw me a diagram of the cash flow of your business?&quot;</p>
<p>The jinn just laughed. &quot;Didn't mean like that, Sara.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;I'd prefer if you not, like, call me that? I didn't give you my name.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Sure, sure. Let's go with&#8230; what are you dressed as, exactly?&quot;</p>
<p>Sara took another swig of her flask. &quot;Tim Allen.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;I don't know who that is, but sure, Ms. Allen, let's go with that.&quot; Some of the fog collected into a reclining chair, which the jinn immediately put to use. &quot;Nah, I ain't here to sell you on an MLM, Ms. Allen. You got friends, talent, and a whole life ahead of you.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Fake, but okay.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;You <em>really</em> oughta believe in yourself, Ms. Allen.&quot; How it kicked its feet up on the fog, Sara was too drunk to care. &quot;All your life you've been honin' yourself like a weapon, ready to strike like a howitzer. You know as well as I do why you ain't fired yet.&quot; A pause. &quot;Emphasis on 'fire'.&quot;</p>
<p>Sara's blood turned to ice.</p>
<p>&quot;I <em>really</em> gotta say I admire your work. Now, I ain't seen it; lookin' through the everything that makes you <em>you</em>, Ms. Allen, I don't know if I need to. People like you, you're the future of humanity.&quot; The jinn made a motion with its hands, like an explosion. &quot;You ain't need to waste away like they've got you doing.&quot;</p>
<p>There was no wind to accompany the fog, but it certainly didn't abate the residual chill. Sara took another swig of her flask. &quot;&#8230; <em>please</em> don't tell me you're reading my mem-&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Rest assured, I have seen <em>nothin'</em>, Ms. Allen. I'm just lookin' at what y'all accomplished, and maybe what y'all <em>want</em> to accomplish.&quot;</p>
<p>Sara cleared her throat. &quot;If this is about the, the <em>camera</em> stuff, like&#8230; I don't know what you're trying to sell me? I mean&#8230; I mean I guess I didn't <em>plan</em> for that stuff, but if you think you're selling me some 'escape', like&#8230; I dunno. I like the work, you know?&quot;</p>
<p>The jinn practically sunk into its recliner of fog. &quot;Sure you do. But-&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Can we skip the 'my looks will fade' shit? I'm prolly gonna be dead in like, a year or something.&quot;</p>
<p>The jinn nodded, maybe, depending on the angle. &quot;I was just wonderin' if you wanted the arson taken off your record. Gives ya' more options, let's you buy guns. In case, maybe you wanna see what accounting's like. The boring, stable stuff.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;But that's gonna cost, like, a lot, right?&quot; Another swig of her flask. &quot;I think I know how this shit works. You're gonna, like, make me ruin my twin sister's life in exchange, right?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;You know what? I was just gonna take your beauty, but that's the <em>perfect</em> price to pay for fixin' up your legals.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Yeah, no. I like Ana. She deserves better.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;What <em>is</em> it with two of y'all havin' sisters named Anna?&quot; Any further into the fog recliner, and the jinn might have been able to make it as a contortionist. &quot;Well, if that's not to your liking, I can still give you a taste of opportunity.&quot;</p>
<p>Oh great, he was going to tempt her or some shit.</p>
<p>&quot;Even better!&quot; It <em>really</em> wasn't fair how much of Sara's internal monologue this thing was privy too. &quot;How about this: I send your resume, and you do have a resume, right, up to the legals in Alagadda. They draft somethin' up, something guaranteed to give you the edge in the market. We send that resume back, you can use it as much or as little as you want.&quot; And Sara barely had time to ask what &quot;the catch&quot; was before the jinn continued. &quot;All I want&#8230; well, I wanna see how much you <em>really</em> like that camera work, yeah?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;I mean, I wouldn't say I '<em>really</em>' like it, but I like it.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Enough to do 24 hours of unpaid work?&quot;</p>
<p>G-d dammit, Sara was right the first time, wasn't she?</p>
<p>&quot;No, no, not like <em>that</em>. I'm just saying&#8230; what if, for the next 24 hours of your work, none of your proceeds make their way into your hands? We'll give you a timer, of course, let you know when it starts makin' you money again, but I <em>really</em> do wanna see if this is a case of 'like'. Then, you got your resume, and the rest of your life ahead of you.&quot;</p>
<p>No. Of course not. This was stupid.</p>
<p>&quot;&#8230; all proceeds go to charity?&quot; But fuck it, Sara had nothing better to do.</p>
<p>If the jinn had a mouth, it'd have been grinning.</p>
<p>&quot;Let's haggle.&quot;</p>
